# Keep all Maven artifacts inside this project so the repo is fully
# self-contained (no dependency on ~/.m2). Helpful for sandboxed runs,
# CI, and the case-study demo.
#
# `${maven.multiModuleProjectDirectory}` resolves to the project root
# (the directory containing this .mvn folder), regardless of where mvn
# is actually invoked from. Without that anchor, a relative path would
# be resolved against the cwd of the mvn invocation.
-Dmaven.repo.local=${maven.multiModuleProjectDirectory}/.m2/repository
